properties.feesApplyText: TENANT INFORMATION Rental payments are taken monthly in advance subject to references and agreed contract terms. Full term payment may be taken in advance subject to references and agreed contract terms. A 6 week deposit is held against dilapidations, this varies subject to the monthly rental, landlords may request a higher deposit amount should pets be permitted at the property. There is an administration fee of £220.00 inc VAT per tenant which covers the cost of requesting references, inventory by an independent professional inventory company, an Assured Shorthold tenancy Agreement and your Deposit Insurance with the Tenancy Deposit Scheme. Should a guarantor be requested (subject to references and landlords instructions) the referencing fees are charged at £50.00 inc VAT per guarantor. A charge of £60 inc VAT per tenancy is charged for any extension of the tenancy agreement for each agreed extension period. A periodic tenancy is extended at a one off fee of £30 inc VAT. An initial holding deposit will be required to reserve the property whilst references are processed. This forms part of the above costs and is subject to the number of tenants per property. Additional charges may apply subject to the terms of the tenancy agreement. For more information please contact Brices Sales and Lettings.
